Possibly invasive species hits ifit seedlings

DAMAGE: A photo provided by the Department of Agriculture shows damage to an ifit stem at the agency's Mangilao nursery. The red buildup at the base of the plant is called "frass," waste produced by stemborer larvae as it feeds inside the stem. Courtesy of the Department of Agriculture

